
Distraction-free view {

  This  refers  to  a  display  mode  where  the  text  is  the major visual
  information  on  the screen. Everything else is switched off:  statusline,
  tabline, vertical splits, etc.

  This offers the user a very powerful tool to concentrate on the code being
  edited.

  The zoom name will be self-explanatory as soon as the plugin is used.

}
Padding buffers       {

  The padding buffers are buffers used to occupy space around the central
  buffer  (zoomed  buffer),   in   order   to  create  the  desired  effect.

}

